<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-18T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-18T13:00:00-05:00" n="236" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d236">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 General Committee/661:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The American Delegate</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-18T19:00:00+01:00">November
                                    18, 1933—7 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 18—4:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>788. For the Under Secretary. Since sending my 7871 am informed that
                            Henderson is inviting the representatives of certain great powers
                            including ourselves with the officers of the Bureau to a “tea party”
                            tomorrow afternoon. I shall accept in line with your 390.</p>
                        <p>I should appreciate an expression of your views for my general
                            guidance.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>